Maybe it was a political killing
or something.

157
00:21:18,380 --> 00:21:19,640
也许吧
Maybe.

158
00:21:19,820 --> 00:21:23,080
也许有人想除掉我们
Maybe someone's picking off
costumed heroes.

159
00:21:23,250 --> 00:21:25,350
你不觉得这话有些偏执吗
DAN:
You don't think that's a little paranoid?

160
00:21:25,520 --> 00:21:28,080
他们就是这么评价我的？
That what they say about me now?

161
00:21:28,330 --> 00:21:29,590
偏执？
Paranoid?

162
00:21:29,760 --> 00:21:32,590
听着，喜剧演员多年来树敌不少
DAN: Look, Comedian made
a lot of enemies over the years...

163
00:21:32,760 --> 00:21:34,250
即使朋友中也有敌人
...even among his friends.

164
00:21:34,430 --> 00:21:36,590
说到朋友，霍利斯・梅森怎么样
RORSCHACH:
Speaking of friends, how's Hollis Mason?

165
00:21:37,470 --> 00:21:41,430
他写过一本书，里面对喜剧演员的评价不高
He wrote that book. Said some bad things
about the Comedian in it.

166
00:21:41,610 --> 00:21:45,670
我不喜欢你说的话，更不喜欢你跟踪我
I don't like what you're implying,
and I like being followed even less.

167
00:21:46,210 --> 00:21:50,670
也许我是在保护你，说不定有人会来追杀你
Maybe I was keeping an eye on you,
in case someone's gunning for masks.

168
00:21:50,850 --> 00:21:55,510
-你不是那种富有感情的人
-袭击一个人，就是袭击我们所有人
-You were never that sentimental.
-Attack on one is attack on all of us.

169
00:21:55,950 --> 00:21:58,390
你觉得我们该怎么办
What do you suggest we do about it?

170
00:21:59,290 --> 00:22:00,450
惩罚
Retribution.

171
00:22:01,860 --> 00:22:05,160
-守望者已经是历史了 -尼克松这么认为
-Watchmen are over.
-Says Tricky Dick.

172
00:22:05,330 --> 00:22:07,090
我这么认为
Says me.

173
00:22:09,700 --> 00:22:11,330
没人知道你的真实面目
Nobody knows who you are.

174
00:22:11,500 --> 00:22:14,470
你可以放弃，过正常人的生活
You can give it up,
try and have a normal life.

175
00:22:14,640 --> 00:22:18,540
你现在过的就是正常人的生活？
That what you have now?
A normal life?

176
00:22:19,540 --> 00:22:22,910
当你走在死于狂犬病的城市街道上
When you walk down the street
in a city dying of rabies...

177
00:22:23,080 --> 00:22:24,550
经过流氓无赖的身边
...past the human cockroaches...

178
00:22:24,720 --> 00:22:27,480
听他们谈论海洛因和幼女色情
...talking about their heroin
and child pornography...

179
00:22:27,650 --> 00:22:29,180
你真觉得正常吗
...do you really feel normal?

180
00:22:30,320 --> 00:22:33,080
至少我不用躲在面具后面
Least I'm not the one
still hiding behind a mask.

181
00:22:34,960 --> 00:22:36,220
不
No.

182
00:22:37,890 --> 00:22:40,020
你是藏在显眼的地方
You're hiding in plain sight.

183
00:22:41,400 --> 00:22:43,560
再见，丹尼尔
Be seeing you, Dan.

184
00:22:44,070 --> 00:22:46,540
维修道通往北面两个街区的地方
A maintenance hatch
will let you out two blocks north.

185
00:22:46,700 --> 00:22:48,430
我记得
Yeah, I remember.

186
00:22:48,610 --> 00:22:52,670
来过多次，那时我们还是搭档
Came here often,
when we were partners.

187
00:22:52,840 --> 00:22:54,740
那是美好的时光，罗夏
DAN: Those were great times, huh,
Rorschach?

188
00:22:55,250 --> 00:22:58,480
-后来呢 -你退出了
-What happened?
-You quit.

189
00:23:21,410 --> 00:23:23,130
罗夏日记
Rorschach 's journal.

190
00:23:23,310 --> 00:23:25,640
第一次拜访徒劳无功
First visit of evening fruitless.

191
00:23:25,810 --> 00:23:27,900
感觉有些压抑
Feel slightly depressed.

192
00:23:28,450 --> 00:23:30,350
很快就会有战争
Soon there will be war.

193
00:23:30,510 --> 00:23:34,080
数百万人将会死于疾病和痛苦
Millions will perish
in sickness and misery.

194
00:23:34,250 --> 00:23:36,780
为什么其中一个人的死就这么重要？
Why does one death matter
against so many?

195
00:23:37,520 --> 00:23:42,320
因为存在正义与邪恶，而邪恶必须被惩罚
Because there is good and evil,
and evil must be punished.

196
00:23:42,490 --> 00:23:45,330
及时世界末日就要来到
Even in the face of armageddon...

197
00:23:45,500 --> 00:23:48,430
我也不会容忍这种事
...I will not compromise in this.

198
00:23:49,000 --> 00:23:50,020
维特先生
MAN:
Mr. Veidt...

199
00:23:50,200 --> 00:23:52,330
到目前为止，你是仅有的两位
...to date,
you ' re one of only two Watchmen...

200
00:23:52,500 --> 00:23:54,940
公开自己守望者身份的人之一
...ever to reveal their true identity
to the world...

201
00:23:55,110 --> 00:23:56,900
第一位是霍利斯・梅森
...the first being Hollis Mason.

202
00:23:57,070 --> 00:24:00,070
你也得到了丰厚的回报
And you've certainly profited greatly
by it...

203
00:24:00,240 --> 00:24:05,510
把你的另一个身份，变成数十亿美元的产业
...turning your superhero alter ego,
Ozymandias, into a billion-dollar industry:

204
00:24:05,680 --> 00:24:08,740
玩具，午餐盒，基因工程
Toys, lunchboxes, genetic engineering.

205
00:24:08,920 --> 00:24:10,980
听说还要拍一部电影
I understand there's a movie
in the works.

206
00:24:11,150 --> 00:24:15,350
-你到底想问什么，罗斯先生 -对不起，你觉得…
-I'm not hearing a question, Mr. Roth.
I'm sorry. Do you think--

207
00:24:15,530 --> 00:24:18,090
守望者会因为我借此发财而恨我？
The Watchmen resent me
for prostituting their struggle?

208
00:24:18,260 --> 00:24:20,990
这是个不错的问题，我也想过
It's a fair question.
Yes, it's crossed my mind...

209
00:24:21,160 --> 00:24:24,190
我原来的一些同事可能会这么认为
...some of my old colleagues
might see it that way...

210
00:24:24,370 --> 00:24:27,360
就像你们知道的那样，有偏见的新闻
...just as you're clearly aware
that biased journalism...

211
00:24:27,540 --> 00:24:30,130
才能让杂志热卖
...sells more magazines.

212
00:24:30,640 --> 00:24:35,410
“维特产业”的销售部门与曼哈顿博士一起提供资金
The merchandising arm of Veidt lndustries
is funding our work with Dr. Manhattan.

213
00:24:35,580 --> 00:24:38,510
我们最近扩建了在南极洲的研究设施
We recently expanded our research facility
in Antarctica...

214
00:24:38,680 --> 00:24:41,910
希望开发出便宜、可再生的能源
...in the hope of developing cheap,
renewable sources of energy...

215
00:24:42,090 --> 00:24:45,080
来消除世界对矿物燃料的依赖
...that we might eliminate
the world's reliance on fossil fuels.

216
00:24:45,260 --> 00:24:47,690
稍有理性的人都能看出
Now, it doesn't take
a political scientist...

217
00:24:47,860 --> 00:24:51,260
我们与苏联的冷战不是意识形态的问题
...to see that our Cold War
with the Russians isn't ideological...

218
00:24:51,430 --> 00:24:54,920
而是因为害怕，害怕不足
...it's based upon fear.
Fear of not having enough.

219
00:24:55,300 --> 00:24:59,000
如果能源是取之不竭的
But if we make resources infinite...

220
00:24:59,170 --> 00:25:01,260
呃
...ah...

221
00:25:01,440 --> 00:25:03,530
战争就会被淘汰
...we make war obsolete.

222
00:25:04,370 --> 00:25:08,210
我希望各地的守望者
I would hope the other Watchmen
understand that...

223
00:25:09,410 --> 00:25:11,070
对此能理解
...wherever they may be.

224
00:25:13,180 --> 00:25:14,550
谢谢你们的时间
Thanks for your time.

225
00:25:20,790 --> 00:25:23,450
-很不错，艾德里安 -丹尼尔
-You look good, Adrian.
-Dan.

226
00:25:23,630 --> 00:25:25,860
久违了
It's been too long.

227
00:25:27,600 --> 00:25:31,660
罗夏认为有人在追捕守望者？
ADRlAN: So Rorschach thinks
someone's hunting the Watchmen, huh?

228
00:25:32,340 --> 00:25:34,200
你觉得这可能吗
You think it's possible?

229
00:25:34,370 --> 00:25:37,100
一桩谋杀不代表一种趋势
Statistically, one murder
doesn't equal a trend.

230
00:25:38,240 --> 00:25:40,210
罗夏是个反社会者，丹尼尔
Rorschach's a sociopath, Dan.

231
00:25:40,840 --> 00:25:44,210
喜剧演员也是，他其实是个纳粹
And so was the Comedian.
He was practically a Nazi.

232
00:25:45,050 --> 00:25:47,070
这点你最清楚
You know that better than anyone.

233
00:25:47,250 --> 00:25:49,450
我不是为他而来
I'm not here because I miss him.

234
00:25:49,620 --> 00:25:50,950
罗夏想到
It's occurred to Rorschach...

235
00:25:51,120 --> 00:25:54,090
我们是唯一知道相互身份的两个人
...that we're the only ones
who know each other's identities.

236
00:25:54,590 --> 00:25:56,680
所有人都知道你的身份
Actually, the whole world knows yours.

237
00:25:57,460 --> 00:25:59,930
所以我第一个来警告你
That's why I'm warning you first.

238
00:26:03,530 --> 00:26:05,520
谢谢你，丹尼尔
Thank you, Dan...

239
00:26:07,140 --> 00:26:10,940
但是我觉得比起罗夏说的杀手
...but I fear there's something
much more real to worry about...

240
00:26:11,110 --> 00:26:13,700
我们更应考虑别的事情
...than Rorschach's mask killer.

241
00:26:15,210 --> 00:26:19,740
如果苏联人发射了核弹，乔真能阻止吗
If the Russians do launch their nukes,
can Jon really stop them?

242
00:26:19,920 --> 00:26:23,550
苏联有51000个核弹头
The Soviets have 51,000
warheads stockpiled.

243
00:26:23,720 --> 00:26:26,920
就算乔拦截了99%
Even if Jon stops 99 percent of them...

244
00:26:27,090 --> 00:26:31,290
剩下的1%仍然能毁灭地球
...the 1 percent that get through
could still kill every living thing on Earth.

245
00:26:34,030 --> 00:26:36,400
曼哈顿博士也不能照顾到所有的地方
Even Dr. Manhattan
can't be everywhere at once.

246
00:26:50,650 --> 00:26:56,280
罗夏日记，1985年10月13日
Rorschach 's journal,
October 13th, 1985...

247
00:26:56,450 --> 00:26:58,790
晚上8点半
...8:30 p.m.

248
00:26:59,490 --> 00:27:03,390
与丹尼尔的会面很不愉快
Meeting with Dreiberg
left bad taste in mouth.

249
00:27:03,590 --> 00:27:07,650
他成了懒散无能、只会在地下室抱怨的人
A flabby failure who sits
whimpering in his basement.

250
00:27:08,830 --> 00:27:11,800
为什么只剩下很少的人能够积极
Why are so few of us left active...

251
00:27:11,970 --> 00:27:16,840
健康、又没有精神障碍？
...healthy and without
personality disorders?

252
00:27:17,010 --> 00:27:20,240
第一个猫头鹰开了家修车行
The first Nite Owl
runs an auto-repair shop.

253
00:27:20,410 --> 00:27:23,810
第一个丝绸鬼魂成了肥胖年老的妓女
The first Silk Spectre
is a bloated, aging whore...

254
00:27:23,980 --> 00:27:26,850
在加利福尼亚的一处疗养地等死
...dying in a California rest resort.

255
00:27:27,020 --> 00:27:29,610
“美元钞票”的披风卡在旋转门里
Dollar Bill got his cape stuck
in a revolving door...

256
00:27:29,790 --> 00:27:31,310
被人当场枪杀了
... where he got gunned down.

257
00:27:31,920 --> 00:27:34,360
“轮廓”，被谋杀了
Silhouette, murdered...

258
00:27:34,690 --> 00:27:37,630
也是她不良生活方式的下场
...a victim of her own indecent lifestyle.

259
00:27:38,190 --> 00:27:41,190
天蛾人现在在缅因州的一家精神病院
Mothman 's in an asylum in Maine.

260
00:27:45,200 --> 00:27:49,400
就连阿德里安・维特，也可能是个同性恋
Even Adrian Veidt, possible homosexual.

261
00:27:49,570 --> 00:27:52,060
必须深入调查
Must investigate further.

262
00:27:52,240 --> 00:27:55,010
我的单子上只剩下两个人
Only two names remain on my list.

263
00:27:55,550 --> 00:28:00,640
都住在洛克菲勒军事研究中心的营房里
Both share private quarters
at Rockefeller Military Research Center.

264
00:28:00,820 --> 00:28:03,150
我应该找他们
I shall go to them.

265
00:28:03,490 --> 00:28:08,860
我应该告诉不可摧毁的人，有人计划谋杀他
I shall go tell the indestructible man
that someone plans to murder him.

266
00:28:09,660 --> 00:28:11,460
晚上好，罗夏
JON:
Good evening, Rorschach.

267
00:28:11,630 --> 00:28:15,120
曼哈顿博士，你知道我何而来
RORSCHACH:
Dr. Manhattan, you know why I'm here.

268
00:28:15,300 --> 00:28:16,730
是的
JON:
Yes...

269
00:28:18,000 --> 00:28:19,970
但是你会失望的离开
...but you're going to leave disappointed.

270
00:28:20,140 --> 00:28:23,870
罗夏，你不该来这里，你正在被通缉
Rorschach. You shouldn't be here.
You're a wanted man.

271
00:28:24,040 --> 00:28:26,240
很高兴见到你，丝绸鬼魂
RORSCHACH:
Nice to see you too, Silk Spectre.

272
00:28:26,410 --> 00:28:28,470
我有真名
I have a real name I've been using.

273
00:28:28,650 --> 00:28:29,670
说说看
Try it.

274
00:28:29,850 --> 00:28:31,940
听你的，劳丽
Whatever you say, Laurie.

275
00:28:32,120 --> 00:28:33,340
你为什么来
What are you doing here?

276
00:28:33,520 --> 00:28:35,850
喜剧演员死了
JON:
The Comedian is dead.

277
00:28:36,020 --> 00:28:38,110
罗夏想让我看看我的未来
Rorschach wants me
to look into my future...

278
00:28:38,460 --> 00:28:40,920
看看凶手有没有查到
...see if the killer is ever
publicly identified.

279
00:28:41,090 --> 00:28:44,190
我已经警告了丹尼尔，再来警告你们
Already warned Dreiberg.
Came to warn you too.

280
00:28:46,900 --> 00:28:49,260
就算我想帮忙
Even if I wanted to help...

281
00:28:49,870 --> 00:28:53,770
我的未来也被某种时间干扰遮住了
...my future is blocked
by some kind of temporal interference.

282
00:28:54,170 --> 00:28:58,230
-我看不清 -干扰？什么造成的
-I cannot see it clearly.
-lnterference? Caused by what?

283
00:28:58,410 --> 00:29:01,810
很可能是核毁灭
In all likelihood, nuclear holocaust.

284
00:29:02,550 --> 00:29:06,640
如果美国与苏联进行全面战争
If the United States and Soviet Union
engage in all-out war...

285
00:29:06,820 --> 00:29:10,810
核爆炸带来的冲击波会产生超光子流
...the resulting blast wave would produce
a sudden burst of tachyons...

286
00:29:10,990 --> 00:29:15,950
它能逆时间而行
...particles which travel backward
through what you perceive as time...

287
00:29:16,590 --> 00:29:19,930
因此遮掩了我对现在的视觉
...therefore obscuring my vision
of the present.

288
00:29:20,730 --> 00:29:22,130
我必须回去工作了
I must return to my work.

289
00:29:22,300 --> 00:29:23,420
等等
RORSCHACH:
Wait a minute.

290
00:29:23,600 --> 00:29:26,090
如果有人因此想除掉我们呢？
What if that's why
someone wants us out of the way?

291
00:29:26,270 --> 00:29:28,500
我们无法阻止吗
So we can't do anything to stop it?

292
00:29:28,670 --> 00:29:30,500
再见，罗夏
Goodbye, Rorschach.

293
00:29:30,670 --> 00:29:32,940
我费了很大劲才进来找到你
RORSCHACH: Took a lot of effort
to get in here to see you.

294
00:29:33,110 --> 00:29:34,440
我不会走的
I'm not leaving--

295
00:29:35,710 --> 00:29:38,040
除非我把话说完
--till I've had my say.

296
00:29:45,560 --> 00:29:48,490
看来最近有很多事你没有告诉我
Seems like there's a lot of things
you don't tell me these days.

297
00:29:48,660 --> 00:29:51,350
我不想过早的警告你
I didn't wanna worry you prematurely.

298
00:29:51,830 --> 00:29:55,960
如果我和艾德里安能解决能源危机，也许战争能避免
If Adrian and I can solve the energy crisis,
war may be averted.

299
00:29:56,130 --> 00:29:58,190
但你一直说时间是同步的
LAURlE:
But you always say time is simultaneous.

300
00:29:58,900 --> 00:30:01,770
如果是这样，你怎能改变未来？
If that's true,
then how can you change the future?

301
00:30:01,940 --> 00:30:06,930
如果你能像我这样看待时间
If only you could perceive time as I do.

302
00:30:07,110 --> 00:30:08,370
我带你看看
Please let me show you.

303
00:30:14,350 --> 00:30:19,290
魔法，梦想，这是我曾经拥有的
我曾是个英雄，该死的
Magic. Dreams. That is what I had before.
I was a hero, goddamn it!

304
00:30:19,460 --> 00:30:22,520
你变老不是我的错，你有什么可抱怨的
It's not my fault you got old.
What do you have to complain about?

305
00:30:22,690 --> 00:30:25,130
我供养着你和孩子
I'm putting food on the table
for you and your child.

306
00:30:25,300 --> 00:30:28,060
给你的朋友艾迪打电话吧，也许他能让你过上更好的生活
Call your friend Eddie.
Maybe he can give you a better life.

307
00:30:28,230 --> 00:30:32,400
-当时是个错误，就那一次 -他想强奸你
-lt was a mistake. One time.
-Man tries to rape you--

308
00:30:32,700 --> 00:30:34,070
停
Stop!

309
00:30:34,840 --> 00:30:36,310
你的思想去了阴暗的地方
Your mind goes to dark places...

310
00:30:36,470 --> 00:30:38,810
你在想我为什么不让你看到接下来的事情
...and you wonder
why I keep the worst from you.

311
00:30:42,750 --> 00:30:46,180
-替我向丹尼尔问好 -什么
-Say hello to Dan for me.
-What?

312
00:30:47,950 --> 00:30:50,750
你想和我一起出去吃饭
You wanna ask me
to go to dinner with you...

313
00:30:52,460 --> 00:30:54,620
像以前那样
...Iike we used to...

314
00:30:56,060 --> 00:30:57,190
但是你不会开口
...but you won't.

315
00:30:57,960 --> 00:31:00,230
你知道我不能去
You know I can't.

316
00:31:02,870 --> 00:31:05,130
所以你会给丹尼尔打电话
So you'll call Dan...

317
00:31:05,570 --> 00:31:07,760
这很正常
...which is only natural.

318
00:31:08,100 --> 00:31:10,700
应该有个老朋友来安慰你
You deserve the comfort of an old friend.

319
00:31:45,010 --> 00:31:46,530
丹尼尔订的桌子
LAURlE:
Dan Dreiberg's table.

320
00:32:07,700 --> 00:32:11,460
你是否知道他和H.J.曾经… -我一点不知道
DAN: Did you know that
he and H.J. were--? I had no idea.

321
00:32:11,970 --> 00:32:15,030
还记得那个疯子吗，他自称什么来着
You remember that crazy guy?
What'd he call himself?

322
00:32:15,210 --> 00:32:16,700
大屠杀队长
Captain Carnage.

323
00:32:16,870 --> 00:32:20,070
经常假装大恶人，好被人痛打一顿
Used to pretend he was a supervillain
just so he could get beat up?

324
00:32:20,240 --> 00:32:22,640
对，有一次在我面前假装，我没有理睬
Yeah, he tried that on me once.
I just walked away.

325
00:32:22,810 --> 00:32:25,840
他就在大白天跟在我身后
He starts following me down the street
in broad daylight...

326
00:32:26,020 --> 00:32:28,810
喊着：“惩罚我，惩罚我！”
...yelling, "Punish me! Punish me!"

327
00:32:29,050 --> 00:32:31,580
我说：“不，走开”
I'm just saying, "No, get lost."

328
00:32:32,720 --> 00:32:35,190
天啊，他后来怎么样了
God, whatever happened to him?

329
00:32:35,360 --> 00:32:37,520
哦，他在罗夏面前玩这一套
Oh. Um....
He pulled that on Rorschach...

330
00:32:37,690 --> 00:32:40,090
被罗夏扔下了电梯井
...and Rorschach
dropped him down an elevator shaft.

331
00:32:46,570 --> 00:32:48,970
天啊，这可一点不好笑
Oh, my God. That's not even funny.

332
00:32:49,670 --> 00:32:52,160
-有一点 -对
-It's a little funny.
-Yep.

333
00:32:54,080 --> 00:32:56,050
很高兴我点了四条腿的鸡
WOMAN: I'm glad I ordered
the four-legged chicken.

334
00:32:56,210 --> 00:32:58,180
能再次见到你真好
It's really good to see you again.

335
00:32:59,420 --> 00:33:00,940
我也是
It's great seeing you too.

336
00:33:01,750 --> 00:33:04,280
我们为什么总是穿得这么正式
Why'd we do it, Dan? Dress up like that?

337
00:33:05,420 --> 00:33:08,750
-别人都不会 -你还记得我的化装服吗
-No one else would.
-Yeah, but do you remember my costume?

338
00:33:08,930 --> 00:33:12,020
满是乳胶的那件，难看死了
All that tight latex?
I mean, it was awful.

339
00:33:12,200 --> 00:33:15,160
是啊，很难看
Uh.... Yeah, yeah, awful.

340
00:33:15,330 --> 00:33:17,770
但是不想让“母亲”失望
But didn't wanna disappoint Mother.

341
00:33:17,930 --> 00:33:21,930
她希望女儿也能像她一样，对抗坏人
Wanted her little girl to be just like her
and fight bad guys.

342
00:33:22,610 --> 00:33:26,200
基恩・艾科特是我们见到的最好的人
I think the Keene Act was the best thing
that ever happened to us.

343
00:33:27,280 --> 00:33:29,640
不过我们这样能活的更长
Well, we'll live longer anyway.

344
00:33:32,950 --> 00:33:34,470
怎么了
What?

345
00:33:35,450 --> 00:33:39,950
乔认为，除非他做些事情
Jon thinks, unless he can do something
about it...

346
00:33:40,790 --> 00:33:42,820
否则将来会有核战争
...that there's gonna be nuclear war.

347
00:33:43,290 --> 00:33:44,780
很快
Soon.

348
00:33:45,660 --> 00:33:49,000
我不太懂，他说的净是些
But I don't know what to think.
I mean, it's all...

349
00:33:49,170 --> 00:33:52,230
量子力学和平行现实之类的术语
...quantum mechanics
and parallel realities with him.

350
00:33:52,400 --> 00:33:55,170
我从不知道他看到的世界是什么样子
I never even know
what universe he's actually seeing.

351
00:33:56,470 --> 00:33:59,600
只是感觉他离我越来越远了
He just keeps getting further away
from me.

352
00:34:00,310 --> 00:34:01,970
对别人也是
Everyone.

353
00:34:03,080 --> 00:34:05,740
我甚至不知道他是否还在乎我
I can't even tell
if he actually cares about me anymore...

354
00:34:05,920 --> 00:34:07,940
还是他假装在乎
...or if he's just pretending.

355
00:34:08,650 --> 00:34:11,590
如果他能假装，说明他还在乎
If he's pretending, it means he cares.

356
00:34:16,330 --> 00:34:18,320
等等，我来开门
Hold on, I'll get the door.

357
00:34:19,660 --> 00:34:21,460
谢谢你，丹尼尔
Thanks, Dan.

358
00:34:21,830 --> 00:34:23,860
-好了吗 -好了
-Got it?
-Yeah.

359
00:34:29,270 --> 00:34:32,260
你吃饭的时候，总有政府人员护送你吗
You always get
a government escort to dinner?

360
00:34:32,980 --> 00:34:37,040
只是为了防止我作出让这个国家最强大的武器难过的事情
They're making sure I don't do anything to
upset the country's most powerful weapon.

361
00:34:38,820 --> 00:34:40,040
对不起
I'm sorry.

362
00:34:40,220 --> 00:34:44,120
我邀请你吃饭叙叙旧，说说高兴的事
I invite you out to dinner to catch up
and have a few laughs...

363
00:34:44,490 --> 00:34:47,850
但是最近没有多少让人高兴的事
...but there don't seem to be many laughs
around these days.

364
00:34:48,020 --> 00:34:51,820
怎么能高兴得起来？喜剧演员死了
What do you expect?
The Comedian's dead.

365
00:36:35,360 --> 00:36:38,930
劳丽，是你吗
Laurie? Is that you?

366
00:36:41,640 --> 00:36:44,610
我以为你已经习惯这样旅行了
Thought you'd be used
to traveling that way by now.

367
00:36:45,270 --> 00:36:49,270
没有，我讨厌乔瞬间传送我
Well, I'm not.
I hate it when Jon teleports me.

368
00:36:49,450 --> 00:36:52,310
比坐飞行的马车要强
Well, it beats flying coach.

369
00:36:52,680 --> 00:36:54,670
喝玛格丽塔吗
Margarita?

370
00:36:54,920 --> 00:36:57,080
母亲，现在是下午两点
Mother, it's 2:00 in the afternoon.

371
00:37:01,920 --> 00:37:04,220
还记得给我写信的那个人吗
Remember that guy
that writes me letters?

372
00:37:04,590 --> 00:37:07,890
他寄给我一件重要的东西，蒂华纳圣经
He sent me an item of memorabilia.
It's a Tijuana bible.

373
00:37:08,060 --> 00:37:12,230
在三四十年代出版的8页的色情漫画
This little eight-page porno comic
they did in the '30s and '40s.

374
00:37:12,400 --> 00:37:16,430
-他寄给你这个？-很有价值，像古董一样
-He sent you this?
-Sure. They're very valuable, like antiques.

375
00:37:17,240 --> 00:37:18,940
母亲，这很下流
Mother, this is gross.

376
00:37:19,110 --> 00:37:21,370
我觉得是一种恭维
I think it's kind of flattering.

377
00:37:21,540 --> 00:37:23,810
你为什么生气的时候，总是叫我母亲？
Why do you always call me Mother
when you're mad?

378
00:37:25,180 --> 00:37:29,240
我知道你为什么来，我仍然能读懂思想
I know why you're here.
I can still read, you know.

379
00:37:30,020 --> 00:37:32,250
我在报纸上看到了
I saw it in the paper.

380
00:37:32,920 --> 00:37:35,820
今天就是艾迪・布莱克的葬礼
Eddie Blake's funeral is today.

381
00:37:37,630 --> 00:37:40,620
他总算是把笑料抖出来了
Finally got his punchline, I guess.

382
00:37:41,100 --> 00:37:43,930
-可怜的艾迪 -他对你那样你还同情他？
-Poor Eddie.
-Poor Eddie? After what he did to you?

383
00:37:44,630 --> 00:37:46,160
劳丽，你还是个孩子
Oh, Laurie, you're still young.

384
00:37:46,940 --> 00:37:48,870
你不明白
You don't know.

385
00:37:49,040 --> 00:37:50,800
事情是会变的
Things change.

386
00:37:51,640 --> 00:37:54,410
那已经是40年前的事了
What happened happened 40 years ago.

387
00:37:54,580 --> 00:37:57,840
我已经67岁了
I'm 67 years old.

388
00:37:58,010 --> 00:38:02,210
每一天，未来都会变得更阴暗一点
Every day, the future
looks a little bit darker.

389
00:38:03,050 --> 00:38:05,210
但是过去
But the past...

390
00:38:05,720 --> 00:38:08,710
就连肮脏的过去
...even the grimy parts of it...

391
00:38:09,260 --> 00:38:11,890
变得越来越清晰
...keep on getting brighter.

392
00:38:17,400 --> 00:38:20,230
闪着眼睛了
I've got spots in my eyes.

393
00:38:23,710 --> 00:38:26,370
少来了，艾迪
Stop it, Eddie.

394
00:38:27,340 --> 00:38:30,710
-谢谢你，维吉 -谢谢你，猫头鹰先生
-Thank you, Weegee.
-Thank you, Mr. Owl.

395
00:38:31,910 --> 00:38:35,110
明天下午3点，到我工作室
Tomorrow, 3:00, my studio.

396
00:38:35,280 --> 00:38:38,450
-21号去小地方 -好
-Little place on 21 st.
-Sounds good.

397
00:38:38,620 --> 00:38:43,220
哇，真正的摄影会，真想看看我的头发会拍成什么样子
SALLY: Wow, a real photo session.
Wonder how my hair will look?

398
00:38:45,530 --> 00:38:48,730
去吧，我五分钟以后到
Oh, go ahead. I'll be there in five.

399
00:39:05,210 --> 00:39:06,240
艾迪
Eddie.

400
00:39:07,320 --> 00:39:11,380
你来干什么，你知道我在换衣服
What the hell are you doing here?
You knew I was changing.

401
00:39:11,550 --> 00:39:13,150
当然知道
Sure I did.

402
00:39:14,790 --> 00:39:16,380
来吧，宝贝
Come on, baby.

403
00:39:16,830 --> 00:39:18,820
我知道你需要什么
I know what you need.

404
00:39:19,000 --> 00:39:23,060
你穿上这样的衣服是有原因的
You gotta have some kind of reason
for dressing in an outfit like this.

405
00:39:23,230 --> 00:39:25,530
我说过不行，艾迪
I said no, Eddie.

406
00:39:26,170 --> 00:39:31,070
-不行就等于同意 -不行就是不行
-No spelled Y-E-S.
-No spelled N-O.

407
00:39:31,240 --> 00:39:34,680
-知道吗 -来吧，亲爱的
-All right?
-Come on, sweetheart.

408
00:39:38,610 --> 00:39:40,210
艾迪
Eddie....

409
00:40:21,060 --> 00:40:23,790
你这混蛋
You little bastard.

410
00:40:30,400 --> 00:40:31,420
你喜欢这样？
This what you like?

411
00:40:31,600 --> 00:40:34,090
-这让你兴奋？-什么
-This what makes you hot?
-What?

412
00:40:44,580 --> 00:40:47,780
没有顺利的事，孩子
Things are tough all over, cupcake.

413
00:40:47,950 --> 00:40:52,050
公平和不公平是同时存在的
It rains on the just and the unjust alike.

414
00:40:52,220 --> 00:40:56,060
喜剧演员算是两者皆备
The Comedian was a little bit of both.

415
00:40:57,530 --> 00:41:00,890
他总是认为他能笑到最后
And he always thought
he'd get the last laugh.

416
00:41:01,430 --> 00:41:04,490
无所不知的上帝，我们心中的秘密
MAN: Thou knowest, Lord,
the secrets of our hearts.

417
00:41:05,100 --> 00:41:08,430
倾听我们的祷告
Shut not thy merciful ears
to our prayers...

418
00:41:08,600 --> 00:41:13,200
宽恕我们，万能的主
...but spare us, Lord most holy,
O God most mighty...

419
00:41:13,380 --> 00:41:16,440
仁慈的救世主
...O holy and merciful savior.

420
00:41:17,110 --> 00:41:19,840
你永恒的判决
Thou most worthy judge eternal.

421
00:41:20,020 --> 00:41:23,350
最后不要让我们受到伤害…
Suffer us not at our last hour
for any--

422
00:42:50,310 --> 00:42:52,740
烟花，不会吧
EDDlE:
Fireworks. You gotta be kidding me.

423
00:42:52,910 --> 00:42:57,640
这个国家怎么会有足够的烟花
You know, you'd think this goddamn
country had had enough fireworks.

424
00:42:58,550 --> 00:43:01,140
如果我们在越南打败了
You know, if we'd lost here in Vietnam...

425
00:43:01,320 --> 00:43:06,280
会把我们国家逼疯
...I think it might have driven us crazy.
You know, as a country.

426
00:43:07,060 --> 00:43:10,750
但是没有打败，多亏了你
But we didn't, thanks to you.

427
00:43:12,730 --> 00:43:14,660
听起来像是挖苦
You sound bitter.

428
00:43:14,830 --> 00:43:16,490
我挖苦了吗？
Me? Bitter?

429
00:43:16,670 --> 00:43:19,730
没有，我觉得很好笑
Fuck, no. I think it's hilarious.

430
00:43:26,080 --> 00:43:27,910
天啊
Oh, Jesus Christ.

431
00:43:28,080 --> 00:43:31,070
-艾迪先生 -正是我最不想看到的
-Mr. Eddie?
-Just what I fucking needed.

432
00:43:31,250 --> 00:43:36,310
战争结束了，我们必须谈谈这个孩子
The war is over now.
We must talk about this baby.

433
00:43:37,090 --> 00:43:40,610
没什么好谈的，我要离开了
There's nothing to talk about.
See, I'm leaving.

434
00:43:40,790 --> 00:43:42,120
我要忘记你
I'm gonna forget about you...

435
00:43:42,290 --> 00:43:45,120
还有这个烂国家
...and your horrible, sweaty,
little piece-of-shit country.

436
00:43:45,690 --> 00:43:46,850
滚出去
Get the fuck out of here.

437
00:43:48,600 --> 00:43:50,460
-不 -滚出去
-No.
-Get the fuck out of here.

438
00:43:50,630 --> 00:43:52,000
你会记住的
You will remember.

439
00:43:53,770 --> 00:43:56,500
你会记住我和我的国家
You will remember me and my country...

440
00:43:57,370 --> 00:43:59,000
永远
...forever!

441
00:44:01,610 --> 00:44:03,480
我的脸
My face!

442
00:44:05,680 --> 00:44:06,840
布莱克，不要
Blake. Don't.

443
00:44:07,650 --> 00:44:08,950
布莱克
Blake!

444
00:44:15,820 --> 00:44:18,320
她怀孕了
She was pregnant...

445
00:44:19,600 --> 00:44:21,320
你打死了她
...and you gunned her down.

446
00:44:21,500 --> 00:44:22,760
是的
That's right...

447
00:44:22,930 --> 00:44:24,870
你就在一边看着
...and you know what? You watched me.

448
00:44:25,030 --> 00:44:28,030
你本可以把枪变成蒸汽，把子弹变成水银
You could have turned the gun to steam,
the bullets to mercury...

449
00:44:28,200 --> 00:44:31,800
把瓶子变成雪花，但是你没有
...the bottle into goddamn snowflakes,
but you didn't, did you?

450
00:44:33,740 --> 00:44:36,580
你对人类一点不在乎
You really don't give a damn
about human beings.

451
00:44:37,750 --> 00:44:40,580
你渐渐失去了人情味，博士
You're drifting out of touch, Doc.

452
00:44:42,150 --> 00:44:44,350
上帝保佑我们
God help us all.

453
00:44:46,360 --> 00:44:47,650
卫生员
Medic!

454
00:44:54,500 --> 00:44:57,660
神圣仁慈的救世主
MAN:
Most holy and merciful savior.

455
00:44:58,600 --> 00:45:03,500
像花朵一样出来，又被割下
He cometh up and is cut down,
like a flower.

456
00:45:03,670 --> 00:45:07,870
在生命的中间，我们在死亡里
In the midst of life, we are in death.

457
00:45:08,040 --> 00:45:12,340
除了你，我们到哪里找到拯救？
Of whom may we seek succor,
but of thee, O Lord?

458
00:45:16,750 --> 00:45:19,810
欢迎，我们很快就开始
Welcome. We'll be starting shortly.

459
00:45:19,990 --> 00:45:22,080
我们再等一个人
We're waiting for one more.

460
00:45:32,870 --> 00:45:36,200
我就说过，你不会是唯一穿着正式的人
I told you, you wouldn't be
the only one dressed up.

461
00:45:37,840 --> 00:45:39,240
欢迎，博士
Welcome, doctor.

462
00:45:39,680 --> 00:45:41,300
现在我们可以开始了
Now we can start.

463
00:45:41,480 --> 00:45:45,310
欢迎前来，现熟悉一下这张高犯罪区域地图
Thank you for coming. Acquaint yourselves
with this map of high-crime areas.

464
00:45:46,680 --> 00:45:47,810
这是胡说
This is all bullshit.

465
00:45:48,620 --> 00:45:52,990
对于自称喜剧演员的人，我不知道你什么时候是在说笑话
For a guy who calls himself the Comedian,
I can never tell when you're joking.

466
00:45:53,160 --> 00:45:56,560
守望者，这是真正的笑话
Watchmen. That's the real joke.

467
00:45:56,730 --> 00:45:59,520
15年前不管用，今天也不会管用
It didn't work 15 years ago,
and it ain't gonna work now...

468
00:45:59,700 --> 00:46:01,820
因为你们想扮演牛仔和印第安人
...because you wanna play
cowboys and lndians.

469
00:46:02,000 --> 00:46:04,360
也许我们开会的时候应该禁止喝酒
Maybe we should agree
on no drinking at meetings.

470
00:46:06,170 --> 00:46:09,900
我和罗夏合作，已经在黑帮的问题上取得了进展
Rorschach and I have made headway
on the gang problem by working together.

471
00:46:10,070 --> 00:46:14,410
这种规模的队伍就像是作秀，我不会参加的
A group this size seems like
a publicity stunt. I'm not in it for the ink.

472
00:46:14,580 --> 00:46:16,370
我们能做得更多
ADRlAN:
We can do so much more.

473
00:46:16,550 --> 00:46:18,740
我们能拯救世界
We can save this world...

474
00:46:20,350 --> 00:46:23,510
-只要有正确的领导 -是啊
-...with the right leadership.
-Yeah.

475
00:46:25,890 --> 00:46:27,650
就是你来领导吧，奥西曼德斯
And that'd be you, right, Ozzy?

476
00:46:27,820 --> 00:46:30,590
你是地球上最聪明的人
I mean, hell,
you're the smartest man on the planet.

477
00:46:30,760 --> 00:46:33,420
只要不是傻子，都能看出世界有麻烦
It doesn't take a genius
to see the world has problems.

478
00:46:33,800 --> 00:46:37,460
但是只有傻子才会认为应该由你来领导
But it takes a room of morons to think
they're small enough for you to handle.

479
00:46:37,970 --> 00:46:39,130
你们
You people.

480
00:46:39,300 --> 00:46:42,760
你听说摩洛回来了，把你们的内裤都拿走了
You hear Moloch's back in town,
get your panties all in a bunch.

481
00:46:42,940 --> 00:46:45,770
-你觉得抓住他重要吗 -重要的是正义
-You think catching him matters?
-Justice matters.

482
00:46:47,340 --> 00:46:49,170
正义
Justice.

483
00:46:49,780 --> 00:46:51,800
我们都会面临审判的
Justice is coming to all of us.

484
00:46:51,980 --> 00:46:53,450
不管我们在做什么
No matter what the fuck we do.

485
00:46:54,180 --> 00:46:58,120
有史以来人类就在相互屠杀
You know, mankind's been trying to kill
each other off since the beginning of time.

486
00:46:58,290 --> 00:47:03,120
现在我们终于有强大的武器来结束屠杀了
Now we finally have the power
to finish the job.

487
00:47:03,360 --> 00:47:06,990
核武器一爆炸，什么都无所谓了，我们都会毁灭
Ain't nothing gonna matter once
those nukes start flying. We'll all be dust.

488
00:47:10,130 --> 00:47:12,160
到时这位奥西曼德斯
Then Ozymandias here...

489
00:47:13,170 --> 00:47:15,430
就会成为废墟里最聪明的人
...will be the smartest man
on the cinder.

490
00:48:04,420 --> 00:48:10,690
守望者，警察，警察保护人民
Watchmen! Police!
Police to protect the people!

491
00:48:15,230 --> 00:48:19,260
请注意，市民们，我们正维护秩序
DAN: Attention, citizens.
We are trying to maintain order.

492
00:48:19,430 --> 00:48:23,870
你们必须离开街道，直到警察罢工结束
You must clear the streets
until the police strike is over.

493
00:48:24,040 --> 00:48:27,200
没必要使用暴力
If you could--
Please, there's no need for violence.

494
