This is twice now
I've ruined your evening.

672
01:03:14,720 --> 01:03:17,710
拜托了,你来我这,我还巴不得呢
Come on. I'm glad you came over.

673
01:03:17,890 --> 01:03:21,410
我正想去霍利斯那里喝点啤酒
I was just gonna see Hollis
for our weekly beer session.

674
01:03:21,590 --> 01:03:23,580
你去的话非常欢迎
You're more than welcome to join.

675
01:03:24,760 --> 01:03:28,060
其实是我想邀请你
In fact, I insist.

676
01:04:00,560 --> 01:04:03,360
曼哈顿博士来了,却没一个人通知我一下
Terrific. Dr. Manhattan arrives
and no one thinks to tell me.

677
01:04:03,530 --> 01:04:05,430
没时间化妆了
WOMAN: He just--
-We don't have time for makeup.

678
01:04:05,600 --> 01:04:07,900
上电视的话,那个蓝色太浅了
That blue is too light for television.

679
01:04:10,670 --> 01:04:12,660
现在够深了吧？
Is that dark enough?

680
01:04:14,480 --> 01:04:17,380
是,是够深了
PRODUCER:
Yeah, that's dark enough.

681
01:04:17,540 --> 01:04:21,210
世界的重担压在他身上，但他会逃避吗？不
MAN: The weight of the world's on him,
but does he quit? No.

682
01:04:21,380 --> 01:04:23,650
新闻供应者永远会面对，他们是…
News vendors always cope. They're the--

683
01:04:23,820 --> 01:04:27,380
天啊，那个流浪汉又来了
Oh, God, here comes
that homeless guy again.

684
01:04:27,820 --> 01:04:30,620
我说过，这月的期刊还没有到
I told you, this month's issue
still hasn't arrived yet.

685
01:04:30,790 --> 01:04:34,450
你为什么在乎右翼分子？那些混蛋才不在乎呢
Why do you care about that right-wing rag?
Those bastards don't give a damn.

686
01:04:35,830 --> 01:04:38,130
等等，他们来了
Hold up. Here they come.

687
01:04:41,900 --> 01:04:44,430
西摩
博尼,把戏练的怎么样了？
-Seymour.
-Bernie, how's tricks?

688
01:04:44,610 --> 01:04:45,630
很好
BERNlE:
Fine, fine.

689
01:04:45,810 --> 01:04:49,110
看见我后面这个人没？
都缠着我一整周了
See this guy behind me?
Been bugging me all week.

690
01:04:52,010 --> 01:04:56,210
也许我们该打辆车，这一片治安不好
Maybe we should get a cab.
These are bad neighborhoods.

691
01:04:56,380 --> 01:05:00,010
我心情不好
Yeah, well, I'm in a bad mood.

692
01:05:12,600 --> 01:05:14,860
有什么好戏看？
Girl.
What we got here?

693
01:05:15,040 --> 01:05:17,900
这是五角大楼核准的不能涉及的几个话题
Here's a list of Pentagon-approved
no-go areas.

694
01:05:18,070 --> 01:05:20,870
肯定会提到阿富汗问题,不要评论的过火
Afghanistan will obviously come up,
but just play it cool...

695
01:05:21,040 --> 01:05:23,410
不要谈论过于敏感的话题
...and try not to get
into any tight corners.

696
01:05:23,580 --> 01:05:27,270
著名核物理学家奥西曼德斯,经历过可怕的事故
--a renowned nuclear physicist,
who, through a terrible accident...

697
01:05:27,450 --> 01:05:33,220
却因祸得福,获得超能力,能用意念来控制物体
...was gifted with extraordinary powers,
capable of bending matter to his will.

698
01:05:33,390 --> 01:05:37,650
世人称他为曼哈顿博士
Today, the world knows him
as Dr. Manhattan.

699
01:05:37,820 --> 01:05:39,160
欢迎
Welcome.

700
01:05:44,160 --> 01:05:45,390
谢谢
JON:
Thank you.

701
01:05:45,570 --> 01:05:47,500
对了
MAN 3:
That's right.

702
01:05:54,040 --> 01:05:56,840
布莱克女士,你可以先发问了
Ms. Black, you have the first question.

703
01:05:57,010 --> 01:05:58,440
曼哈顿博士,如你所知
Dr. Manhattan, as you know...

704
01:05:58,610 --> 01:06:01,310
“末曰之钟”象征着
...the Doomsday Clock
is a symbolic clock face...

705
01:06:01,480 --> 01:06:05,040
人类接近毁灭的时间
...analogizing humankind's proximity
to extinction...

706
01:06:05,390 --> 01:06:08,380
午夜代表了核战
...midnight representing the threat
of nuclear war.

707
01:06:08,560 --> 01:06:11,720
现在的时间是午夜前四分钟
As of now, it stands at four minutes
to midnight.

708
01:06:12,360 --> 01:06:14,830
您觉得我们正处在灭绝的边缘吗？
Would you agree that we're that close
to annihilation?

709
01:06:15,230 --> 01:06:17,560
我父亲曾是个钟表匠
My father was a watchmaker.

710
01:06:18,400 --> 01:06:22,730
自从爱因斯坦发现时间的相对性
他就放弃了这一工作
He abandoned it when Einstein discovered
that time is relative.

711
01:06:23,900 --> 01:06:25,900
我只能说，一个象征意义的钟
I would only agree
that a symbolic clock...

712
01:06:26,070 --> 01:06:28,060
对于智者的作用
...is as nourishing to the intellect...

713
01:06:28,240 --> 01:06:31,510
如同一张氧气照片对于快淹死的人的作用
...as a photograph of oxygen
to a drowning man.

714
01:06:33,850 --> 01:06:35,580
你的意思是，不存在什么危险？
So you're saying there is no danger.

715
01:06:35,750 --> 01:06:39,740
即使没有核武器，世界仍然有危险
JON: Even in a world without nuclear
weapons, there would still be danger.

716
01:06:44,690 --> 01:06:47,590
你是否同意很多人的观点
MAN:
And would you say, as so many claim...

717
01:06:47,760 --> 01:06:49,520
说你实际上是个神
...that you are, in fact, a god...

718
01:06:49,700 --> 01:06:52,530
因为你能同时看见过去和未来
...given you see the past
and future simultaneously?

719
01:06:52,700 --> 01:06:55,000
我只能看见我自己的过去
I can only see my own past...

720
01:06:55,440 --> 01:06:59,340
至于我的未来,我也不是什么都知道
...my own future. I am not omniscient.

721
01:06:59,940 --> 01:07:01,310
罗斯,该你提问了
KOPPEL:
Doug Roth, your question?

722
01:07:01,480 --> 01:07:04,210
说到您的过去,曼哈顿博士…
Speaking of your past, Dr. Manhattan...

723
01:07:04,380 --> 01:07:07,140
您还记得叫沃利・韦沃尔的人吗？
...do you remember a man
named Wally Weaver?

724
01:07:07,310 --> 01:07:12,450
是,我们都是吉拉研究基地的物理学家
Yes. We were both physicists together
at the Gila Flats Research Base.

725
01:07:12,950 --> 01:07:14,510
他死于癌症
He died of cancer.

726
01:07:15,390 --> 01:07:17,650
-他是个好人 -那么埃德加・雅各比呢
-He was a good man.
How about Edgar Jacobi...

727
01:07:17,820 --> 01:07:20,730
也被称为大恶人摩洛
...also known as the supervillain Moloch?

728
01:07:21,700 --> 01:07:25,790
在60年代你们见过几次面
You encountered him several times
in the '60s: battles, conflicts.

729
01:07:26,000 --> 01:07:28,470
您是否知道他也得了癌症？
Did you know that he has cancer as well?

730
01:07:29,400 --> 01:07:30,630
没人对我说过
I wasn't told.

731
01:07:30,800 --> 01:07:33,030
那蓝道夫将军呢？
And what about
General Anthony Randolph?

732
01:07:33,210 --> 01:07:36,640
您起初为政府工作时,他就是你的上司
He was your handler when you first
started working for the government.

733
01:07:37,040 --> 01:07:38,070
也得了癌症
Cancer.

734
01:07:38,250 --> 01:07:40,910
你是说我导致了癌症
You're suggesting I was the cause.

735
01:07:41,310 --> 01:07:44,310
在我看来,这是毫无疑问的
From where I'm standing,
it's starting to look pretty conclusive.

736
01:07:44,480 --> 01:07:46,510
即使这样，也是不相干的
JON:
Even if that's the case, it's irrelevant.

737
01:07:46,690 --> 01:07:49,490
完好的人类身体,和受疾病侵袭的人类身体
A live human body
and a deceased human body...

738
01:07:49,660 --> 01:07:51,750
都有着相同数量的微粒
...have the same number of particles.

739
01:07:54,490 --> 01:07:56,390
身体结构上没有什么不同
Structurally, there' s no difference.

740
01:07:57,530 --> 01:07:59,800
好的,请安静一下
All right. Let's settle down, please.

741
01:08:05,670 --> 01:08:06,900
那珍妮・斯雷特呢？
What about Janey Slater?

742
01:08:07,670 --> 01:08:10,010
你觉得她不一样？
You think it makes a difference to her?

743
01:08:11,080 --> 01:08:12,410
珍妮？
Janey?

744
01:08:12,750 --> 01:08:14,300
你的前女友
Your ex-girlfriend?

745
01:08:14,480 --> 01:08:18,110
她也是个物理学家,你们已经认识11年了
She was a physicist too.
You saw each other for 11 years.

746
01:08:18,290 --> 01:08:19,810
一次只能问一个问题
Doug, one question at a time.

747
01:08:19,990 --> 01:08:23,350
她也患了癌症,医生说,她只有6个月可以活了
She has cancer as well.
Doctors have given her six months.

748
01:08:23,520 --> 01:08:25,350
对吧,斯雷特小姐？
Isn't that right, Miss Slater?

749
01:08:40,870 --> 01:08:42,670
乔,你曾是我的全部
You were the world to me, Jon.

750
01:08:43,280 --> 01:08:45,510
你曾是我的生命
You were my whole life.

751
01:08:46,450 --> 01:08:49,040
还记得你说过多少遍爱我吗？
Do you remember how many times
you said you loved me?

752
01:08:49,220 --> 01:08:50,910
珍妮,我不知道你病了
Janey, I wasn't told.

753
01:08:51,380 --> 01:08:56,750
事故之后我一直支持你,我给了全部
I stuck by you after the accident.
I gave you everything.

754
01:09:01,800 --> 01:09:03,460
你就这样“报答”我？
This is how you repay me?

755
01:09:03,900 --> 01:09:08,800
珍妮,我真的不知道
去你的吧,乔,上帝诅咒你
-Janey, I wasn't told. I didn't know.
-Damn you, Jon. Goddamn you.

756
01:09:08,970 --> 01:09:10,960
珍妮,等等
Janey, wait.

757
01:09:12,370 --> 01:09:14,810
结束了,访谈结束
-That's it. This interview is over.
-Get up there.

758
01:09:14,980 --> 01:09:17,340
把摄像机关了,所有人后退
Get those cameras off.
Everybody back off.

759
01:09:17,510 --> 01:09:21,210
所有人后退,我需要点后援,放开他
Everybody back off.
I need some backup here. Leave him alone.

760
01:09:21,380 --> 01:09:27,480
拜托了,大家都各自散了吧
Please, if everyone
would just go away...

761
01:09:27,650 --> 01:09:30,560
别来烦我
...and leave me alone....

762
01:09:30,720 --> 01:09:32,120
你愿意发表评论吗？
Do you care to comment?

763
01:09:32,290 --> 01:09:35,320
我说了,别来烦我
I said, leave me alone!

764
01:10:00,950 --> 01:10:02,850
天啊
Jesus.

765
01:10:03,960 --> 01:10:05,550
我们
Us...

766
01:10:06,460 --> 01:10:08,290
被抢劫了
...getting mugged.

767
01:10:10,630 --> 01:10:12,220
我们走
Let's go.

768
01:10:17,970 --> 01:10:19,770
我很震惊
I'm shaking.

769
01:10:23,980 --> 01:10:25,740
你知道吗
You know what?

770
01:10:26,110 --> 01:10:29,600
我累了，今天就这样吧
I'm wiped. I'm just gonna call it a night.

771
01:10:29,780 --> 01:10:33,010
你真的不想和我一起到霍利斯那里吗
Oh, are you sure you don't wanna
come by Hollis' with me...

772
01:10:33,190 --> 01:10:35,420
去消遣一下？
...and shake off the adrenaline?

773
01:10:36,220 --> 01:10:39,350
今晚我已经见到足够的英雄行为了
LAURlE: I think I've had enough hero stuff
for one night.

774
01:10:40,490 --> 01:10:42,860
你能倾听就很有帮助了
It helped having you listen.

775
01:10:43,160 --> 01:10:44,890
我的荣幸
DAN:
Any time.

776
01:10:45,600 --> 01:10:47,500
保重，丹尼尔
LAURlE:
Take care, Dan.

777
01:10:48,300 --> 01:10:50,600
这是残酷的世界
It's a rough world out there.

778
01:10:52,070 --> 01:10:53,270
再见
DAN:
Be seeing you.

779
01:10:57,610 --> 01:10:58,740
我们晚了
You're late.

780
01:10:58,910 --> 01:11:02,010
我知道，你不会相信发生了什么事
Ah, I know. I know.
You won't believe what happened.

781
01:11:02,180 --> 01:11:04,980
曼哈顿博士在电视直播中大发脾气
Dr. Manhattan just lost it on live TV.

782
01:11:05,150 --> 01:11:06,850
等等，什么？
Wait, what?

783
01:11:12,430 --> 01:11:14,360
我当时和劳丽在一起，她不知道
I was just with Laurie. She doesn't know.

784
01:11:15,160 --> 01:11:18,760
她很快就会知道的，整个世界都会知道
HOLLlS: She's gonna know soon enough.
The whole world will know.

785
01:11:18,930 --> 01:11:21,660
我说了,别来烦我
I said, leave me alone!

786
01:11:31,510 --> 01:11:33,710
我正在抬头看星星
JON:
I am looking at the stars.

787
01:11:34,210 --> 01:11:36,210
它们如此的遥远
They're so far away...

788
01:11:36,650 --> 01:11:39,310
发出的光经过这么多年才到达地球
...and their light takes so long
to reach us...

789
01:11:42,060 --> 01:11:46,250
我们看见的星星,只是它们的老照片
...all we ever see of stars
are their old photographs.

790
01:11:49,860 --> 01:11:53,700
1959年,7月,我恋爱了
It is July, 1959, and I am in love.

791
01:11:54,530 --> 01:11:56,200
太好了
MAN:
That' s great.

792
01:11:56,370 --> 01:11:58,000
你明天过来拿吧 好的
-You can pick it up tomorrow.
-Okay.

793
01:11:58,170 --> 01:11:59,900
75美分 好的,谢谢你
-Seventy-five cents.
-Okay, thank you.

794
01:12:00,070 --> 01:12:01,100
谢谢
Thank you.

795
01:12:01,270 --> 01:12:05,470
惨了,乔,我真希望他能给点暗示
我肯定扮鬼脸了
Gosh, Jon, I wish he gave us a little notice.
I'm sure I made a face.

796
01:12:05,650 --> 01:12:10,640
不用了,你肯定你很美
Oh, no, no.
I'm sure that you'll look beautiful.

797
01:12:14,550 --> 01:12:16,890
她叫 珍妮 斯雷特
Her name is Janey Slater.

798
01:12:17,720 --> 01:12:20,390
和我一样,她是个物理学家
She is a physicist, like me.

799
01:12:21,660 --> 01:12:23,420
我那年30岁
I am 30 years old.

800
01:12:28,130 --> 01:12:32,070
是我们大学校友沃利介绍的
We were introduced by a good friend
of mine from college, Wally Weaver.

801
01:12:36,240 --> 01:12:38,800
1981年 2月12号
It is February 12th, 1981.

802
01:12:38,980 --> 01:12:42,750
沃利死于癌症,现在他们说是我导致的
Wally dies of cancer,
of which they now say I am the cause.

803
01:12:59,730 --> 01:13:03,130
那晚,我和珍妮第一次做爱
That night, Janey and I make love
for the first time.

804
01:13:10,980 --> 01:13:13,970
一个月后,一场灾难等着我
A month from now,
the accident awaits me.

805
01:13:21,450 --> 01:13:24,950
我会赶上你们的,我的手表落里面了
Oh, I'll catch up with you guys.
I think I left my watch inside.

806
01:13:25,630 --> 01:13:27,860
我们等一会
Hey. Let's just wait a second.

807
01:13:31,260 --> 01:13:35,670
我穿过了屋子,找到了手表
I cross the room to the
Intrinsic Field Center. I find my watch.

808
01:13:42,380 --> 01:13:43,540
我到门口的时候
When I get to the door...

809
01:13:45,310 --> 01:13:46,510
沃利脸都变白了
... Wally is turning white.

810
01:13:46,680 --> 01:13:50,740
程序已经被锁定,定时器是打不开的
The program's locked in.
We can't override the time lock.

811
01:13:52,120 --> 01:13:54,050
我害怕极了
I am terrified.

812
01:13:54,220 --> 01:13:55,350
乔？
JANEY:
Jon?

813
01:14:00,590 --> 01:14:02,360
抱歉,乔
I'm sorry, Jon...

814
01:14:04,300 --> 01:14:05,860
我不能…
...but I can't--

815
01:14:08,130 --> 01:14:09,660
珍妮,别离开我
Janey, don't leave me!

816
01:14:10,200 --> 01:14:12,190
别离开我
Don't leave me!

817
01:14:44,240 --> 01:14:49,000
1959年,5月12号,我和珍妮在别人的撮合下见面了
It is May 12th, 1959,
when I'm introduced to Janey.

818
01:14:49,440 --> 01:14:51,640
她请我喝了杯啤酒
She buys me a beer...

819
01:14:51,850 --> 01:14:54,680
第一次有女人请我喝啤酒
...the first time a woman
has done this for me.

820
01:14:56,050 --> 01:14:59,880
她把凉凉的啤酒递给我时
As she passes me the cold,
perspiring glass...

821
01:15:00,520 --> 01:15:01,750
我们的指尖接触了
...our fingers touch.

822
01:15:14,630 --> 01:15:16,800
对,乔,好的
Yes, Jon, good.

823
01:15:16,970 --> 01:15:22,470
下面就是如何按照正确的顺序，把零件再组装起来
Now it' s just a question of reassembling
the components in the correct sequence.

824
01:15:26,310 --> 01:15:27,400
我最后一次
I feel fear...

825
01:15:28,650 --> 01:15:30,780
感受到了恐惧
...for the last time.

826
01:15:47,600 --> 01:15:50,030
举行了一场象征性的葬礼
A token funeral is held.

827
01:15:50,200 --> 01:15:52,360
没有可以埋葬的遗体
There is nothing to bury.

828
01:15:52,540 --> 01:15:55,130
珍妮把照片放在相框里
Janey frames the snapshot.

829
01:15:55,340 --> 01:15:58,470
这是我唯一的照片
It's the only photograph of me
anyone has.

830
01:15:59,780 --> 01:16:04,650
围墙外,是个循环系统
A circulatory system is seen
by the perimeter fence.

831
01:16:05,050 --> 01:16:06,520
几天后
A few days later...

832
01:16:06,690 --> 01:16:09,920
一个有部分肌肉的骨架站在了走廊里
...a partially muscled skeleton
stands in a hallway...

833
01:16:10,090 --> 01:16:13,920
尖叫了一会就消失了
...and screams for a moment
before vanishing.

834
01:16:39,290 --> 01:16:41,310
哦,神啊
Oh, God.

835
01:16:41,490 --> 01:16:43,010
乔？
Jon?

836
01:16:44,060 --> 01:16:45,890
是你吗？
Is that you?

837
01:16:46,560 --> 01:16:49,590
世界各国都从今早的消息中震惊了
Nations around the world
reeling from this morning's announcement...

