爱德华・布莱克,那个喜剧演员
她有一万个理由恨他
...Edward Blake, the Comedian,
a man she has every reason to hate...

1667
02:32:54,910 --> 02:32:58,900
出于对这种深不可测的几率的一种反叛
...and out of that contradiction,
against unfathomable odds...

1668
02:32:59,580 --> 02:33:01,480
才有了你
...it's you--

1669
02:33:03,220 --> 02:33:04,550
独一无二的
Only...

1670
02:33:05,220 --> 02:33:06,710
你
...you.

1671
02:33:07,550 --> 02:33:08,820
出生在这个世界上
--that emerged.

1672
02:33:09,390 --> 02:33:13,880
把如此与众不同的相貌
To distill so specific a form...

1673
02:33:14,060 --> 02:33:16,320
从所有错乱的基因中提取出来
...from all that chaos...

1674
02:33:18,230 --> 02:33:21,200
就像是把空气变成了金子
...is like turning air into gold.

1675
02:33:25,570 --> 02:33:27,560
简直就是奇迹
A miracle.

1676
02:33:31,080 --> 02:33:32,570
因此
And so...

1677
02:33:33,080 --> 02:33:34,910
我的确错了
...I was wrong.

1678
02:33:36,920 --> 02:33:40,750
擦干眼泪,我们回去吧
Now dry your eyes, and let's go home.

1679
02:34:08,280 --> 02:34:12,310
表层受压了,温度超高
We got a bearing on that artificial structure.
Heat signature's off the charts.

1680
02:34:13,290 --> 02:34:16,380
维特
我不喜欢阿基摇摇晃晃的
-Veidt.
-I don't like the way Archie's kicking.

1681
02:34:24,800 --> 02:34:27,630
引擎 引擎出毛病了,赶紧抓牢了
-The engines.
-They're icing up. Hold onto something.

1682
02:34:28,400 --> 02:34:30,430
丹尼尔,我们飞的太低了
Daniel, you're coming in too low.

1683
02:34:33,310 --> 02:34:36,470
别打乱我,赶紧飞高点
Don't wish to interfere,
but perhaps should pull up sharply--

1684
02:34:36,640 --> 02:34:40,580
我知道,我正在试着飞高点,我操
I know! I'm trying.
I'm trying to pull him up, goddamn it!

1685
02:35:07,840 --> 02:35:11,470
我正试着改变尾焰排出的路径,来降低温度
DAN: I'm gonna redirect the heat from
the flamethrower to speed up deicing...

1686
02:35:11,640 --> 02:35:14,510
不过得需要一会时间,我们没有时间了
...but it's gonna take a while
and we don't have time to wait.

1687
02:35:16,020 --> 02:35:17,480
你得多穿点取暖
You need something warmer.

1688
02:35:18,020 --> 02:35:20,180
我穿这就不冷
Fine like this.

1689
02:35:49,680 --> 02:35:51,550
怎么了,宝贝？
What is it, girl?

1690
02:35:53,850 --> 02:35:55,550
嗯
Mm.

1691
02:36:21,150 --> 02:36:23,410
阿德丽安是和平主义者
DAN:
Adrian's a pacifist.

1692
02:36:23,620 --> 02:36:28,250
他是个素食主义者,一生中都没有杀生过
He's a vegetarian, for chrissakes.
He's never killed anyone in his life.

1693
02:36:28,420 --> 02:36:29,820
希特勒也是素食主义者
Hitler was vegetarian.

1694
02:36:29,990 --> 02:36:34,520
你太谨慎了,把他交给我吧,我们不会
有第二次机会了
You're squeamish, leave him to me.
We won't get second chance.

1695
02:37:46,670 --> 02:37:48,000
先生们
Gentlemen.

1696
02:37:48,500 --> 02:37:52,440
欢迎欢迎 阿德丽安,我们都知道了
-Welcome.
-Adrian, we know everything.

1697
02:37:52,600 --> 02:37:54,370
那,还有什么好说的
Then what's there to discuss, Dan?

1698
02:37:54,540 --> 02:37:57,530
要说的多着呢,是你杀了喜剧演员
Plenty. You killed Comedian.

1699
02:37:57,710 --> 02:37:59,230
希望他能安息
May he rest in peace.

1700
02:37:59,750 --> 02:38:02,340
是布莱克首先想明白的
Blake figured it out first.

1701
02:38:02,510 --> 02:38:06,580
尼克森一直监视着我们,防止我们搞破坏
Nixon had him keeping tabs on us,
making sure we weren 't rocking the boat.

1702
02:38:07,520 --> 02:38:09,780
布莱克发现了我来卡纳克的目的
Blake found out what I was doing
here in Karnak...

1703
02:38:09,960 --> 02:38:14,020
他去拜访可怜的摩洛,他已经快不行了
...and by the time he visited poor Moloch,
he was cracking badly.

1704
02:38:14,190 --> 02:38:17,460
连我都无法想象他会改变主意
Even I couldn't predict he'd be the one
to have a change of heart.

1705
02:38:18,200 --> 02:38:19,720
于是
So...

1706
02:38:20,770 --> 02:38:22,700
我不得不杀他灭口
...I had to kill him.

1707
02:38:23,270 --> 02:38:27,030
然后我摆平了乔,真不是件容易活
Then I neutralized Jon. No easy task.

1708
02:38:27,210 --> 02:38:29,670
我花了20亿,来研究超光速粒子
I put roughly $2 billion
into tachyon research...

1709
02:38:29,840 --> 02:38:31,870
来阻断乔对未来的预测
...to block Jon's vision of the future.

1710
02:38:32,040 --> 02:38:34,310
你利用他的心理档案来操纵他
RORSCHACH: You used his psych profile
to manipulate him.

1711
02:38:34,810 --> 02:38:36,280
让他离开了这个星球
Got him to leave the planet.

1712
02:38:36,450 --> 02:38:39,850
我认识乔很长时间了,知道他总是无法
摆脱情绪的困扰
I've known Jon long enough
to see he isn't devoid of emotion.

1713
02:38:40,020 --> 02:38:43,920
他微妙的面部变化,对门外汉来说可能
可以瞒过去,不过对我来说…
His subtle facial twitches wouldn't be
noticed by the layman, but to me...

1714
02:38:44,090 --> 02:38:45,920
他可能还抽噎过
...he might as well have been sobbing.

1715
02:38:46,290 --> 02:38:49,420
我所需要的就是沿着这条线索往下
All I needed to do was tug on the thread.

1716
02:38:49,590 --> 02:38:51,490
当他认为使心爱的人患上了癌症
The sudden flood of emotion Jon felt...

1717
02:38:51,660 --> 02:38:55,260
乔所感受到的那种突然的感情袭击
...when he came to believe
he 'd given cancer to the people he loved...

1718
02:38:55,430 --> 02:38:57,560
才是他真正离开地球的原因
... was all the excuse he needed
to leave Earth.

1719
02:38:57,740 --> 02:39:01,570
你的杀手,你雇他干掉我们
DAN: Your bullshit assassin.
You paid him to throw us off.

1720
02:39:01,740 --> 02:39:06,400
丹,德斯先生的死是为了更崇高的目的
ADRlAN: Mr. Chess gave his life
in the service of a higher cause, Dan.

1721
02:39:08,550 --> 02:39:11,640
我让他吃下去了个氰化物胶囊
I put a cyanide capsule in his mouth...

1722
02:39:11,820 --> 02:39:14,410
只留下一个漏点
...Ieaving only one loose end:

1723
02:39:15,020 --> 02:39:18,460
那就是,你和你的面具杀手理论
You, and your mask-killer theory...

1724
02:39:18,620 --> 02:39:21,750
你坚持不懈的跟踪一个真正的反社会人
...one you followed
with the tenacity of a true sociopath.

1725
02:39:21,930 --> 02:39:23,620
我给警察提供了线索
I tipped off the police.

1726
02:39:23,800 --> 02:39:26,200
你入狱的时候,我才能更好的行动
Once you were in prison,
I was able to move forward.

1727
02:39:26,360 --> 02:39:28,990
抱歉让你失望了
Sorry to disappoint you.

1728
02:39:42,180 --> 02:39:44,650
我们本该为地球谋福利
DAN: We were supposed to make the world
a better place.

1729
02:39:44,820 --> 02:39:46,550
丹,我现在正是在为地球谋福利
ADRlAN:
Dan, that's exactly what I am doing.

1730
02:39:46,720 --> 02:39:48,050
核战？
DAN:
Nuclear war?

1731
02:39:48,220 --> 02:39:50,380
灭绝人类？
Human extinction?

1732
02:40:00,030 --> 02:40:04,930
当然了,不过只是几个地区而已
ADRlAN: Of course, my moral safeguards
gave me pause at the necessary sacrifice.

1733
02:40:05,100 --> 02:40:08,070
全球的几个重要的地区
A few key regions around the globe--

1734
02:40:08,240 --> 02:40:13,700
纽约,洛杉矶,莫斯科,香港
New York, Los Angeles, Moscow,
Hong Kong.

1735
02:40:13,880 --> 02:40:15,540
将会立即分解
--disintegrated in an instant.

1736
02:40:16,280 --> 02:40:19,610
1500万人将死于非命
Fifteen million people killed...

1737
02:40:19,790 --> 02:40:21,840
这都是曼哈顿博士一手策划的
...by Dr. Manhattan himself.

1738
02:40:23,050 --> 02:40:25,850
这是第三次世界大战对地球的惩罚
The world's punishment
for flirting with World War lll.

1739
02:40:26,020 --> 02:40:27,150
乔是不会这么做的
Jon wouldn't do that.

1740
02:40:27,730 --> 02:40:30,420
而事实只有我们三个人知道
A fact no one outside this room
ever has to know.

1741
02:40:31,060 --> 02:40:34,860
我一直致力的能源大突破也已经初见成效了
The energy breakthrough I was working on
just came to fruition.

1742
02:40:35,470 --> 02:40:39,460
这些年来,乔一直在帮我复制他的能量
All these years, Jon was helping me
replicate his power...

1743
02:40:39,640 --> 02:40:42,160
而却不知道我到底打算怎么利用这些能量
...unaware of how I planned to use it.

1744
02:40:42,340 --> 02:40:44,330
知道嘛
You see...

1745
02:40:45,240 --> 02:40:47,640
喜剧演员说的对
...the Comedian was right.

1746
02:40:48,350 --> 02:40:53,340
人性的残忍将终会导致全球灭亡
Humanity's savage nature
will inevitably lead to global annihilation.

1747
02:40:53,520 --> 02:40:56,320
所以为了征求这个地球
So in order to save this planet...

1748
02:40:56,590 --> 02:40:58,650
我必须得用
...I had to trick it...

1749
02:40:59,020 --> 02:41:03,050
人类史上最伟大的恶作剧来解决此事
...with the greatest practical joke
in human history.

1750
02:41:03,330 --> 02:41:06,730
-杀死数百万人 -来拯救数十亿人
-Killing millions.
-To save billions.

1751
02:41:07,270 --> 02:41:09,230
必要的犯罪
A necessary crime.

1752
02:41:09,400 --> 02:41:11,560
我们不会让你得逞的
RORSCHACH:
You know we can't let you do that.

1753
02:41:13,000 --> 02:41:15,130
“得逞”？罗夏
"Do that," Rorschach?

1754
02:41:15,310 --> 02:41:16,930
我不是连环画里的恶棍
I'm not a comic-book villain.

1755
02:41:17,780 --> 02:41:20,040
我有必要给你们解释我的大师之笔吗？
Do you think
I'd explain my masterstroke to you...

1756
02:41:20,210 --> 02:41:24,380
如果你们能,哪怕一丁点,影响到我的计划
...if there were even the slightest possibility
you could affect the outcome?

1757
02:41:27,120 --> 02:41:29,920
35分钟前我就启动了这一切
I triggered it 35 minutes ago.

1758
02:43:09,390 --> 02:43:12,380
神啊,亨利
Jesus Christ, Henry.

1759
02:43:12,560 --> 02:43:14,750
我们为什么就不发射个侦探卫星？
Why the hell
didn't we get a launch detection?

1760
02:43:16,660 --> 02:43:21,100
这不是苏联
It's not the Soviets, sir.

1761
02:43:21,670 --> 02:43:24,830
这都需要能源签章
Intel indicates the energy signature...

1762
02:43:25,000 --> 02:43:27,440
是由曼哈顿博士
...was generated by...

1763
02:43:28,410 --> 02:43:30,840
签名才有效
...Dr. Manhattan.

1764
02:43:33,680 --> 02:43:35,240
乔
Jon.

1765
02:43:38,250 --> 02:43:39,380
干涉
Interference.

1766
02:43:39,990 --> 02:43:41,890
大范围干涉
Cataclysmic interference.

1767
02:43:51,600 --> 02:43:54,360
简直无法置信,这真的发生了
LAURlE:
I can't believe it happened.

1768
02:43:55,370 --> 02:43:58,860
这不是核战引发的
This wasn't caused by nuclear warheads.

1769
02:44:02,940 --> 02:44:04,240
是我
It was me.

1770
02:44:06,280 --> 02:44:07,870
我
I...

1771
02:44:08,450 --> 02:44:09,470
我一手造成的
...did this.

1772
02:44:10,120 --> 02:44:13,570
你什么意思？这是你造成的？
间接造成的
-What do you mean, you did this?
-Not directly.

1773
02:44:14,550 --> 02:44:17,250
看起来像是我造成的
It was made to look like I did it.

1774
02:44:20,290 --> 02:44:21,720
阿德丽安
Adrian.

1775
02:44:28,000 --> 02:44:29,990
说曹操 曹操到
Speak of the devil.

1776
02:44:33,140 --> 02:44:34,160
-乔 -我知道
DAN: Jon--
JON: I know.

1777
02:44:34,340 --> 02:44:36,500
一定要阻止他,杀了布莱克,杀了数以百万的人
RORSCHACH: Must stop him.
Killed Blake, killed millions.

1778
02:44:36,670 --> 02:44:38,010
在这等着
Wait here.

1779
02:44:49,150 --> 02:44:51,520
住手吧,阿德丽安
Adrian, stop this.

1780
02:44:52,990 --> 02:44:54,860
超光速粒子很聪明
The tachyons were clever...

1781
02:44:55,990 --> 02:45:00,330
即便我无法预测你在哪,我也能把这些墙弄粉碎
...but even if I can't predict where you are,
I can turn the walls to glass.

1782
02:45:01,670 --> 02:45:04,130
我该谢谢你
I should thank you.

1783
02:45:05,300 --> 02:45:08,500
我差点忘了那种快感…
I'd almost forgotten the excitement
of not knowing...

1784
02:45:09,510 --> 02:45:12,500
对未来不确定的快乐
...the delights of uncertainty.

1785
02:45:16,680 --> 02:45:18,340
原谅我,宝贝
Forgive me, girl.

1786
02:45:41,310 --> 02:45:43,000
你真是个混蛋
You're such an asshole.

1787
02:46:16,940 --> 02:46:18,880
维特,你这个混蛋
DAN:
Veidt, you bastard.

1788
02:46:19,040 --> 02:46:21,510
你要敢伤害她,我…
丹
-lf you've hurt her, I'll--
-Dan...

1789
02:46:23,250 --> 02:46:27,840
醒醒吧,我的新世界不需要这么多的英雄主义
...grow up. My new world
demands less obvious heroism.

1790
02:46:28,020 --> 02:46:30,010
你的
Your...

1791
02:46:30,190 --> 02:46:35,150
那一套英雄主义太多余了
你们有什么成就吗？
...schoolboy heroics are redundant.
What have they achieved?

1792
02:46:36,760 --> 02:46:39,630
还是没能拯救地球
Failing to prevent Earth's salvation...

1793
02:46:40,600 --> 02:46:43,000
这就是你们唯一的功绩
...is your only triumph.

1794
02:46:43,200 --> 02:46:45,100
我对你失望透顶了,阿德丽安
JON:
I'm disappointed in you, Adrian.

1795
02:46:45,900 --> 02:46:49,400
我很失望
I'm very disappointed.

1796
02:47:01,790 --> 02:47:04,950
我学到的第一个花招,就是重组我自己
Reassembling myself
was the first trick I learned.

1797
02:47:05,620 --> 02:47:08,020
这是杀不了奥斯特曼的
It didn't kill Osterman.

1798
02:47:10,630 --> 02:47:12,990
你真的觉得这能置我于死地？
Did you really think it would kill me?

1799
02:47:14,300 --> 02:47:17,460
我在太阳表面都行走过
I have walked across the surface
of the sun.

1800
02:47:17,970 --> 02:47:21,130
我目睹了如此小又如此快速的事情
I have witnessed events
so tiny and so fast...

1801
02:47:21,310 --> 02:47:24,370
简直就是白驹过隙
...they can hardly be said
to have occurred at all...

1802
02:47:24,540 --> 02:47:28,170
不过你,阿德丽安,你只是个凡人而已
...but you, Adrian, you're just a man.

1803
02:47:29,310 --> 02:47:31,810
世上最智慧的人
The world's smartest man...

1804
02:47:32,120 --> 02:47:34,550
对我构成的威胁
...poses no more threat to me...

1805
02:47:34,720 --> 02:47:37,850
就和最智慧的白蚁对我的威胁一样大
...than does its smartest termite.

1806
02:47:40,120 --> 02:47:41,590
这是什么？
What's that?

1807
02:47:41,990 --> 02:47:43,860
又一个终极武器？
Another ultimate weapon?

1808
02:47:44,500 --> 02:47:46,220
是
Yes.

1809
02:47:47,830 --> 02:47:49,300
可以这么说
You could say that.

1810
02:47:52,840 --> 02:47:54,770
…遭受攻击
--came under attack.

1811
02:47:55,610 --> 02:47:58,940
数以万计的人死于非命
Millions of lives were suddenly ended...

1812
02:47:59,280 --> 02:48:04,480
这是曼哈顿博士自己犯下的罪恶
...in an act of evil
perpetrated by Dr. Manhattan himself.

1813
02:48:06,280 --> 02:48:10,220
自从攻击开始的一刻,我就一直和
Since the attacks,
I have been in constant contact...

1814
02:48:10,390 --> 02:48:13,380
苏联总理密切通信
... with the premier of the U. S. S.R.

1815
02:48:13,790 --> 02:48:16,620
不计前嫌
Putting aside our past differences...

1816
02:48:16,960 --> 02:48:19,120
我们都同意合伙
... we have both pledged to unite...

1817
02:48:19,460 --> 02:48:22,800
来对付这个共同的敌人
...against this common enemy.

1818
02:48:23,300 --> 02:48:25,290
同世界所有人一起
With the rest of the world...

1819
02:48:25,740 --> 02:48:27,760
我们会胜利
... we will prevail.

1820
02:48:30,310 --> 02:48:33,300
今天,我们将永远铭记
This is a day we shall never forget.

1821
02:48:33,480 --> 02:48:37,680
我们会继续保护人类
And yet we go forward
to defend the human race...

1822
02:48:37,850 --> 02:48:42,480
保护所有正义和美好的事情
...and all that is good
and just in our world.

1823
02:48:43,820 --> 02:48:48,050
谢谢,上帝保佑我们
Thank you. God bless us all.

1824
02:48:48,430 --> 02:48:50,220
看见没？
ADRlAN:
Do you see?

1825
02:48:52,430 --> 02:48:54,900
两个超级大国,从战争中撤离出来
Two superpowers retreating from war.

1826
02:48:56,500 --> 02:48:58,940
我把地球从水深火热中拯救了出来
I've saved the earth from hell.

1827
02:48:59,100 --> 02:49:01,070
我们俩都是
We both have.

1828
02:49:01,540 --> 02:49:03,730
对你我来说,同是胜利
This is as much your victory as it is mine.

1829
02:49:08,550 --> 02:49:10,040
我们现在能重新回去
Now we can return...

1830
02:49:11,480 --> 02:49:13,040
干我们该干的事了
...do what we were meant to.

1831
02:49:13,220 --> 02:49:16,190
我们需要正义
We were meant to exact justice.

1832
02:49:16,520 --> 02:49:19,850
人人都将知道你干了什么好事
会吗？
-Everyone's gonna know what you've done.
-Will they?

1833
02:49:20,020 --> 02:49:24,830
揭发我的话,你就会葬送
这么多人的死所带来的和平
By exposing me, you would sacrifice
the peace so many died for today.

1834
02:49:25,000 --> 02:49:28,430
和平却建立在谎言的基础上
不过和平
-Peace based on a lie.
-But peace...

1835
02:49:28,600 --> 02:49:30,790
虽然如此… 他说的没错
-...nonetheless.
-He's right.

1836
02:49:31,370 --> 02:49:35,330
揭发阿德丽安只会让世界重新陷入到核战中去
Exposing Adrian would only doom the world
to nuclear destruction again.

1837
02:49:35,510 --> 02:49:38,370
我们不能这样做
No. We can't do this.

1838
02:49:38,540 --> 02:49:40,310
在火星上
On Mars...

1839
02:49:41,810 --> 02:49:43,640
你教会了我生命的意义
...you taught me the value of life.

1840
02:49:44,620 --> 02:49:47,050
如果我们想让生命在这里继续流传下去
If we hope to preserve it here...

1841
02:49:47,850 --> 02:49:49,880
就必须保持沉默
...we must remain silent.

1842
02:49:53,730 --> 02:49:55,660
自己保守好秘密
Keep your own secrets.

1843
02:50:02,530 --> 02:50:03,730
想都别想
Don't even think about it.

1844
02:50:06,340 --> 02:50:08,070
罗夏
Rorschach.

1845
02:50:09,840 --> 02:50:11,370
等等
Wait.

1846
02:50:12,410 --> 02:50:14,500
永不妥协
Never compromise.

1847
02:50:14,880 --> 02:50:17,750
即使是面临世界末日
Not even in the face of armageddon.

1848
02:50:18,150 --> 02:50:21,140
这是我们俩的区别,丹尼尔
That's always been the difference
between us, Daniel.

1849
02:50:32,200 --> 02:50:35,720
我感受过死亡
I've made myself feel every death...

1850
02:50:37,200 --> 02:50:43,110
我看见为了拯救人类,而杀死的所有无辜的人
...see every innocent face
I've murdered to save humanity.

1851
02:50:48,680 --> 02:50:52,380
-你都理解的,是吧？-没有宽恕
-You understand, don't you?
JON: Without condoning...

1852
02:50:54,050 --> 02:50:55,950
没有谴责
...or condemning...

1853
02:51:00,360 --> 02:51:02,290
我理解
...I understand.

1854
02:51:09,700 --> 02:51:12,830
让开,人们应该知道真相
Out of my way. People have to be told.

1855
02:51:13,700 --> 02:51:15,640
你知道我不会让你这么做的
You know I can't let you do that.

1856
02:51:16,870 --> 02:51:19,870
你突然间发现了人性？
Suddenly you discover humanity?

1857
02:51:21,310 --> 02:51:23,140
真是时候
Convenient.

1858
02:51:31,860 --> 02:51:36,420
如果你一开始就关心的话
这一切就都不会发生了
If you'd cared from the start,
none of this would have happened.

1859
02:51:40,200 --> 02:51:43,170
我能改变一切
I can change almost anything...

1860
02:51:47,740 --> 02:51:50,070
不过不能改变人类的本性
...but I can't change human nature.

1861
02:51:51,410 --> 02:51:54,810
当然了,你必须得保护维特的新乌托邦
Of course
you must protect Veidt's new utopia.

1862
02:51:56,080 --> 02:51:59,410
为这个根基,多死一个人又怎样？
What's one more body
amongst foundations?

1863
02:52:05,590 --> 02:52:07,460
你还等什么？
Well, what are you waiting for?

1864
02:52:10,930 --> 02:52:12,760
动手吧
Do it.

1865
02:52:18,870 --> 02:52:19,890
动手吧
Do it!

1866
02:52:22,610 --> 02:52:25,970
不
No!

1867
02:52:43,460 --> 02:52:49,230
我离开这个星系,去一个不这么复杂的地方
JON: I'm leaving this galaxy
for one a little less complicated.

1868
02:52:49,400 --> 02:52:51,890
我以为你又一次在意生命呢
LAURlE: I thought you said you cared
about life again.

1869
02:52:52,070 --> 02:52:53,470
我真的这样认为
JON:
I do.

1870
02:52:54,810 --> 02:52:57,710
或许我得再创造点生命
I think maybe I'll create some.

1871
02:53:01,810 --> 02:53:04,140
保重,劳丽
Goodbye, Laurie.

1872
02:53:39,380 --> 02:53:40,540
还手啊
Come on.

1873
02:53:43,020 --> 02:53:44,610
还手啊
Come on!

1874
02:53:49,030 --> 02:53:50,360
丹
Dan...

1875
02:53:50,830 --> 02:53:53,590
世界的联合与和平
...a world united and at peace.

1876
02:53:54,470 --> 02:53:55,660
必须有人作出牺牲
There had to be sacrifice.

1877
02:53:55,830 --> 02:54:00,200
不,你没有把人类理想化,你让人类变形了
No! You haven't idealized mankind,
you've deformed it.

1878
02:54:00,370 --> 02:54:02,130
残缺了
You've mutilated it.

1879
02:54:02,510 --> 02:54:04,670
这是你的遗产
That's your legacy.

1880
02:54:13,220 --> 02:54:16,020
这是个真实的恶作剧
That's the real practical joke.

1881
02:55:08,610 --> 02:55:12,600
重申一下,你的电视机没有任何的毛病
MAN [ON TV] : We repeat, there is
nothing wrong with your television set.

1882
02:55:12,780 --> 02:55:16,240
你现在即将参与一场伟大的探险活动
You are about to participate
in a great adventure.

1883
02:55:16,410 --> 02:55:19,580
将要体验威严和神秘的历程
You are about to experience
the awe and mystery...

1884
02:55:19,750 --> 02:55:25,550
从内到外的历程
... which reaches from the inner mind
to the outer limits.

1885
02:55:26,760 --> 02:55:28,950
不喝点什么吗？
SALLY:
Sure you don ' t want a drink?

1886
02:55:29,960 --> 02:55:30,980
不用了
I ' m okay.

1887
02:55:32,060 --> 02:55:33,290
干杯
Cheers.

1888
02:55:34,730 --> 02:55:37,860
有些事情,不说不快
There's something I need
to get off my chest.

1889
02:55:39,140 --> 02:55:41,630
我知道艾迪布莱克是我的亲生父亲
I know that Eddie Blake was my father.

1890
02:55:44,640 --> 02:55:46,410
劳丽
Laurel.

1891
02:55:47,410 --> 02:55:49,740
你肯定对我有想法
What you must think of me.

1892
02:55:50,580 --> 02:55:53,110
抱歉,我一直都瞒着你
I'm sorry I never told you.

1893
02:55:53,280 --> 02:55:55,080
我早该
I should have...

1894
02:55:55,250 --> 02:55:59,380
我不知道该怎么办,我觉得很丢人,很傻
...but I don't know, I just felt ashamed.
I felt stupid.

1895
02:55:59,560 --> 02:56:01,490
没关系了
It doesn't matter.

1896
02:56:02,330 --> 02:56:07,590
是命运让人们去些奇怪的地方
干些奇怪的事情
People's lives take them strange places.
They do strange things...

1897
02:56:08,170 --> 02:56:11,100
然后无法诉说
...and, well,
sometimes they can't talk about them.

1898
02:56:11,270 --> 02:56:13,600
我知道这种感觉
I know how that is...

1899
02:56:14,340 --> 02:56:16,930
不过我想让你知道
...but I just want you to know...

1900
02:56:17,510 --> 02:56:20,340
你对我却从来没做过错事
...that you never did anything wrong
by me.

1901
02:56:24,520 --> 02:56:28,780
你问了我为什么我从来不生他的气
You asked me why I wasn't mad at him.

1902
02:56:30,350 --> 02:56:32,850
因为他让我生了你
Because he gave me you.

1903
02:56:37,860 --> 02:56:38,950
谢谢你,妈妈
Thanks, Mom.

1904
02:56:41,700 --> 02:56:43,500
我爱你
I love you.

1905
02:56:51,040 --> 02:56:55,240
你好,朱庇特 哦,萨拉,是你啊
-Hello, Miss Jupiter.
-Oh, Sally, please.

1906
02:56:56,880 --> 02:57:01,480
打扰了,我得出去透透气了,一会就会来
Excuse me. Gotta go freshen up.
I'll be right back.

1907
02:57:12,000 --> 02:57:16,160
你这怎么样了？很好啊,你那呢？
-So how's it going up here?
-Good. How's it going down there?

1908
02:57:16,330 --> 02:57:19,830
很好,我觉得一切都恢复正常了
Good. I think I've got everything working.

1909
02:57:20,000 --> 02:57:24,630
阿基的系统都升级了,现在都已经完成了
All of Archie's systems are upgraded.
Finished the tinkering for now...

1910
02:57:24,810 --> 02:57:27,040
现在要做的,就是骑它出去兜圈风
...so all we gotta do is take her out.

1911
02:57:27,210 --> 02:57:30,270
哇,听起来像是个约会哦
Well, that sounds like a date.

1912
02:57:41,590 --> 02:57:43,860
我们会没事的,是吗？
Are we gonna be all right?

1913
02:57:45,930 --> 02:57:50,230
只要大家还一直认为乔在看着我们
我们就不会有事
Long as people think Jon's
still watching us, we'll be all right...

1914
02:57:50,430 --> 02:57:52,300
噩梦都过去了
...in the end.

1915
02:57:53,940 --> 02:57:56,100
我知道乔会怎么说:
I know what Jon would say:

1916
02:57:56,270 --> 02:57:58,300
事情总是没有尽头的
Nothing ends.

1917
02:58:00,210 --> 02:58:02,810
总是没有尽头的
Nothing ever ends.

1918
02:58:50,160 --> 02:58:53,930
西摩,我们都没有题材可以写了
Seymour, we got nothing
to write about anymore.

1919
02:58:54,100 --> 02:58:55,460
国家内的每个人
Everyone in the country...

1920
02:58:55,630 --> 02:58:57,900
世界上的每个国家都手拉着手
...every country in the world
are holding hands...

1921
02:58:58,070 --> 02:59:01,330
唱着和平友爱的歌
...and singing songs
about peace and love.

1922
02:59:01,840 --> 02:59:04,710
感觉像是住在一个超和平的社区内
It's like living in a goddamn
global hippie commune.

1923
02:59:04,880 --> 02:59:08,810
呃,里根说他要在88年竞选总统
Well, Ronald Reagan says he's gonna
be running for president in '88.

1924
02:59:08,980 --> 02:59:10,810
我们来报道这个吧
We could run a piece on that.

1925
02:59:10,980 --> 02:59:14,140
西摩,荒谬的话我们是不能拿来做头条的
Seymour, we don't dignify absurdities
with coverage.

1926
02:59:14,320 --> 02:59:18,150
这还是在美国,谁会想听
白宫里的有个西部牛仔的故事？
This is still America, damn it.
Who wants a cowboy in the White House?

1927
02:59:18,890 --> 02:59:23,120
要不然我去档案里再去找点劲爆的？
Okay. I could look for something
in the crank file.

1928
02:59:23,290 --> 02:59:24,890
档案里面？
Crank file.

1929
02:59:25,060 --> 02:59:27,050
随便了,找点原创的
Whatever. Take some initiative.

1930
02:59:27,230 --> 02:59:29,860
想写什么就写什么,全交给你了
Run whatever you like.
I leave it entirely in your hands.

1931
02:59:36,370 --> 02:59:41,070
罗夏日记,1985年,10月12号
Rorschach 's journal, October 1 2th, 1 985.

1932
02:59:41,250 --> 02:59:45,710
今晚,喜剧演员死于纽约
Tonight, a comedian died in New York.

1933
